  "text": "Assessing instrumental use of knowledge can also be done by measuring adherence to recommendations or quality indicators. Grol [CITATION_1] completed a series of studies involving family physicians in the Netherlands who recorded their adherence to 30 national guidelines. Three hundred forty-two indicators of adherence were constructed and physicians received educational sessions on how to record their performance on these indicators. Computer software was developed to relate performance to clinical conditions to assess adherence. [CITATION_2] More simply, we could look at how often we prescribe β-blockers in appropriate patients with heart failure through a chart-based audit.",
